        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "refactor(whatsapp): introduce inbound message contexts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR reorganizes WhatsApp `WebInboundMessage` so inbound callback data is grouped by what the data represents instead of being exposed only as one large flat object.\n\nThe new shape separates inbound message facts into five explicit contexts:\n\n- `event`: message id, timestamp, and batching metadata\n- `payload`: message body, media, location, and structured payload context\n- `quote`: quoted/replied-to message context\n- `group`: group subject, participants, and mention metadata\n- `platform`: WhatsApp transport details and actions such as reply, media send, and typing\n\nDownstream WhatsApp auto-reply, monitor, identity, group gating, reaction, reply delivery, media, quote, and test-support code now reads these facts from the new contexts. The shipped flat callback fields and methods remain available as deprecated aliases so existing callback consumers can upgrade without a breaking shape change.\n\n## API Shape\n\nCode that receives a WhatsApp inbound message should prefer the relevant context, for example `msg.payload.body`, `msg.event.id`, `msg.group?.mentions`, `msg.quote?.body`, and `msg.platform.reply(...)`.\n\nFor compatibility, existing flat callback fields and methods such as `msg.body`, `msg.chatId`, `msg.reply(...)`, and `msg.mediaPath` are still populated and marked deprecated in the exported `WebInboundMessage` type.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/src/monitor-inbox.behavior.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound.media.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Review Note\n\nThe inbound callback contract now exposes the nested context shape while preserving the shipped flat callback aliases. The runtime only creates optional contexts when their facts exist, so non-media messages do not expose a truthy `payload.media` and direct debounced batches do not expose a truthy `group` context.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp inbound callback messages now expose event, payload, quote, group, and platform contexts while preserving deprecated flat aliases for the shipped callback contract.\n\nReal environment tested: Local focused WhatsApp extension tests.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: The commands listed in Verification were run after the final patch.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused WhatsApp inbox and media tests passed, whitespace diff check passed, and autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: Inbound monitor and auto-reply tests consume the nested message contexts for body, media, quote, group, event, platform reply, media send, and typing behavior, while fallback flat aliases remain populated.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live WhatsApp device/session behavior and broad Testbox/CI lanes.\n",
